27:52.737 --> 27:53.987
Tell me more.

27:55.188 --> 27:57.804
Aeo, seven years ago,

27:57.806 --> 28:00.722
he shows up with a case full of money.

28:00.724 --> 28:04.210
I was supposed to do my job
on you and take the girl.

28:04.212 --> 28:05.848
It was my part in his little plan.

28:05.850 --> 28:10.765
But you were already gone,
and so the plan changed.

28:10.767 --> 28:11.734
ULY: Go on.

28:11.736 --> 28:13.547
I don't know anymore, it's all I know.

28:13.549 --> 28:14.516
Aeo has Penelope?

28:14.518 --> 28:16.940
- I don't know, ask him.
- Tell me more!

28:16.942 --> 28:18.672
POPOV: I can't, I can't
tell you what I don't know.

28:18.674 --> 28:20.484
Tell me more motherfucker!

28:20.486 --> 28:24.818
- (BLADE WHIRRING)
- Leave him to me.

28:34.916 --> 28:37.166
I have a few questions too.

28:38.334 --> 28:42.917
No, no, no, no, no, no,
don't leave me here ike this.

28:47.786 --> 28:50.363
You gonna be alright?

28:50.365 --> 28:51.532
Who are you?

28:54.669 --> 28:55.752
I'm no one.

28:57.488 --> 29:00.988
(POPOV BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:05.906 --> 29:08.573
(CLOCK TICKING)

29:09.825 --> 29:12.825
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

29:27.014 --> 29:27.845
- You know.
- Darling.

29:27.847 --> 29:29.502
If you wanted to see me,

29:29.504 --> 29:31.552
you could have just called or come by.

29:31.554 --> 29:32.524
OCEAN: Penelope.

29:32.526 --> 29:34.885
Instead, two gangsters
show up at my front door,

29:34.887 --> 29:36.233
hustle me.

29:36.235 --> 29:38.020
And your dog has nothing to say.

29:38.022 --> 29:39.635
You told me to bring her.

29:39.637 --> 29:42.554
We have a very sensitive problem.

29:44.260 --> 29:48.995
I'm sorry that sometimes
the nature of my business

29:48.997 --> 29:51.349
means that you have to deal with this.

29:51.351 --> 29:52.309
PENELOPE: What happened?

29:52.311 --> 29:53.142
Look, we're only trying

29:53.144 --> 29:54.977
- to protect you.
- Out.

30:02.412 --> 30:06.557
Tomorrow is the
anniversary of Taurus city.

30:06.559 --> 30:08.544
Every 10 years I have the possibility...

30:08.546 --> 30:10.546
To celebrate yourself.

30:11.386 --> 30:14.197
It is very important to me.

30:14.199 --> 30:17.949
But I know that maybe
someone would hurt you.

30:19.403 --> 30:21.870
And my first thought
was to bring you here,

30:21.872 --> 30:24.166
where I can protect you.

30:24.168 --> 30:25.585
Is that so wrong?

30:27.168 --> 30:30.335
Isn't that how any father would react?

30:37.544 --> 30:41.044
(UPBEAT ELECTRONIC MUSIC)

31:28.268 --> 31:31.518
Welcome to Cacao Island, home of Aeo.

31:34.149 --> 31:37.732
God of winds and dear
to the immortal gods.

31:39.845 --> 31:44.095
Revere him, it's your only
hope on this long night.

31:46.769 --> 31:50.352
(DRAMATIC CLASSICAL MUSIC)

32:06.943 --> 32:10.443
(UPBEAT ELECTRONIC MUSIC)

32:37.867 --> 32:39.950
Get the fuck off, shit!

32:42.756 --> 32:43.589
Johnny?

32:44.751 --> 32:46.167
Where's Penelope?

32:55.681 --> 32:56.514
Go out.

32:58.088 --> 32:59.338
Where is she?

33:08.536 --> 33:11.536
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

33:16.545 --> 33:21.189
Ms. Vasilescu, I understand
you've been through a lot.

33:21.191 --> 33:22.886
We gotta ask you a few questions.

33:22.888 --> 33:25.555
(PHONE RINGING)

33:31.457 --> 33:34.392
No, he's talking to a witness.

33:34.394 --> 33:35.894
Send it to me now.

33:36.729 --> 33:38.999
Okay, keep us posted.

33:39.001 --> 33:42.562
So the landlord found
his name, Johnny Ferro.

33:42.564 --> 33:44.487
(PHONE BEEPS)

33:44.489 --> 33:45.822
Do you know him?

33:51.865 --> 33:55.032
Ms. Vasilescu, is this the same guy?

33:56.873 --> 33:58.456
Yeah, that's him.

33:59.527 --> 34:01.801
That's Mr. No One.

34:01.803 --> 34:03.136
DEFILN: What?

34:04.750 --> 34:06.844
He's the one who saved my life.

34:06.846 --> 34:07.725
You're sure?

34:07.727 --> 34:09.301
This man saved your life?

34:09.303 --> 34:11.408
Yeah, I swear.

34:11.409 --> 34:14.766
MARINO: Shit, get this
picture to every cop in the city.

34:14.768 --> 34:16.246
Where are we going?

34:16.248 --> 34:18.915
MARINO: Same place as Johnny.

34:31.042 --> 34:33.415
(SNIFFING)

34:33.417 --> 34:35.500
(GROANS)

34:50.527 --> 34:52.445
Stop calling me that.

35:10.423 --> 35:11.590
Seven years.

35:31.530 --> 35:33.863
Is that why you fucked me?

36:24.483 --> 36:28.900
I guess you would have
been the one getting fucked.

36:47.443 --> 36:50.860
The fuck am I supposed to do with this?

36:51.899 --> 36:53.004
I'm not your runner anymore.

36:53.006 --> 36:55.923
We don't have time for this shit.

37:45.190 --> 37:46.940
Don't fuck with me.

37:52.909 --> 37:54.659
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

37:57.114 --> 37:58.531
How's the fish?

37:59.885 --> 38:03.436
You still get it from that old Greek?

38:03.438 --> 38:08.438
No, he retired, his nephew
now, nice man, young family.

38:08.794 --> 38:12.127
He brings it here, brings what he likes.

38:16.443 --> 38:19.443
How do you make it sound so civil?

38:20.319 --> 38:21.152
What?

38:23.417 --> 38:26.534
He brings it, because if he doesn't pay

38:26.536 --> 38:28.619
the price of his freedom,

38:30.127 --> 38:33.755
the great Ocean would have
his deliveries delayed,

38:33.757 --> 38:37.054
his employees bullied at the market

38:37.056 --> 38:41.707
and his nice young family
harassed and terrorized,

38:41.709 --> 38:44.792
until he either goes out of business,

38:45.737 --> 38:48.070
or kneels to kiss your feet.

38:49.819 --> 38:52.902
Everything you have is built on fear.

38:55.432 --> 38:57.764
This fish is on your plate

38:59.985 --> 39:03.358
because he ate the other smaller fish

39:03.360 --> 39:07.615
until he became big, and
strong enough to swim free

39:07.617 --> 39:11.950
and get caught in the net
and brought to the market.

39:15.242 --> 39:19.242
I'm not the fish, or the
net, or the fishmonger.

39:23.345 --> 39:24.678
I am the market.

39:32.419 --> 39:34.809
NIKO: It's a setup, Uly, it's gotta be.

39:34.811 --> 39:35.874
ULY: I have no choice.

39:35.876 --> 39:37.975
You get caught with that shit.

39:37.977 --> 39:39.089
Throw that shit away.

39:39.091 --> 39:40.617
That doesn't get me
any closer to Penelope.

39:40.619 --> 39:42.286
Neither does this.

39:44.020 --> 39:46.353
Listen, we'll take it slow,

39:46.355 --> 39:48.891
find all the ways in and all the ways out.

39:48.893 --> 39:50.310
Tactical recon.

39:51.707 --> 39:52.849
The last time we followed that plan,

39:52.851 --> 39:55.768
it didn't work out so well, did it?

39:57.906 --> 40:02.573
Sometimes you have to make
a decision, right or wrong.

40:03.930 --> 40:07.609
And live or die with the consequences?

40:07.611 --> 40:10.944
(WAVES CRASHING SOFTLY)

40:16.683 --> 40:18.596
This life that you think you live,

40:18.598 --> 40:20.765
this normal you crave for.

40:23.378 --> 40:25.074
That is the lie.

40:25.076 --> 40:27.230
I do not accept that.

40:27.232 --> 40:31.005
You say that I built my life on fear;

40:31.007 --> 40:35.757
I fear that I will never again
have the love of my child.

40:45.606 --> 40:47.721
You blame me for Johnny.

40:47.723 --> 40:49.044
Tomorrow would have been...

40:49.046 --> 40:50.955
I know you do.

40:50.957 --> 40:54.426
You had to have someone
to blame, so why not me?

40:54.428 --> 40:55.259
Papa.

40:55.261 --> 40:58.094
He never came back from the war.

41:02.709 --> 41:04.644
He came to me.

41:04.646 --> 41:06.873
He begged for a chance to work,

41:06.875 --> 41:09.208
a chance to provide for you.

41:13.570 --> 41:18.487
"Husband to father," he said,
"for the woman we both love."

41:21.282 --> 41:23.365
NIKO: What's the plan?

41:24.479 --> 41:26.538
Go in the back.

41:26.540 --> 41:28.957
They have to think I'm alone.

41:32.260 --> 41:33.093
Johnny.

41:34.833 --> 41:37.833
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

41:41.753 --> 41:45.253
The last time your position was no better.

42:15.166 --> 42:17.499
(GUN FIRES)

42:19.427 --> 42:21.177
I did not kill him.

42:24.954 --> 42:28.115
I wouldn't kill my daughter's husband.

42:28.117 --> 42:31.784
Even if I hated him,
even if he betrayed me.

42:37.108 --> 42:40.525
There are things that even I wouldn't do.

42:44.207 --> 42:46.540
Then what happened to him?

42:49.752 --> 42:50.752
Who knows?

42:58.820 --> 43:01.329
Oh my God, oh my God!

43:01.331 --> 43:03.414
Oh my God, oh my God, no.

43:05.310 --> 43:08.477
- No, no, no, no.
- It's not your fault.

43:14.217 --> 43:15.050
I'm sorry.

43:20.574 --> 43:22.991
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

43:26.186 --> 43:27.769
No, no, no, no, no.

43:29.885 --> 43:33.143
(DELFIN SOBBING)

43:33.145 --> 43:36.145
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

43:42.094 --> 43:42.927
Oh shit.

43:45.063 --> 43:45.896
Uly, move!

44:03.353 --> 44:06.103
(DOG WHIMPERING)

44:07.196 --> 44:09.613
(SOFT MUSIC)

44:30.287 --> 44:33.424
Shit, don't sneak up on me like that!

44:33.426 --> 44:34.259
Sorry.

44:36.484 --> 44:37.901
Where were you?

44:39.046 --> 44:39.879
Here.

44:42.249 --> 44:44.416
I was here the whole time.

44:46.993 --> 44:48.076
What's wrong?

44:50.839 --> 44:51.672
Nothing.

44:54.250 --> 44:56.000
Just in my own world.

45:10.196 --> 45:13.083
Maming that psycho was one
thing, but killing a cop?

45:13.085 --> 45:14.074
ULY: It was an accident.

45:14.076 --> 45:15.886
They're not gonna make that distinction.

45:15.888 --> 45:17.460
They're gonna hunt you down.

45:17.462 --> 45:19.629
- They already are.
- Uly!

45:20.516 --> 45:21.349
Let it go!

45:23.137 --> 45:25.470
It's too big, it's too much!

45:26.424 --> 45:28.605
Don't you see that?

45:28.607 --> 45:30.524
She thinks you're dead!

45:32.334 --> 45:33.772
Has it crossed your mind
that maybe the best thing...

45:33.774 --> 45:35.223
I have to find Penelope.

45:35.225 --> 45:36.624
- Then what?
- She'll know the truth.

45:36.626 --> 45:38.626
What's the truth, Uly?

45:39.550 --> 45:40.550
What's true?

45:41.923 --> 45:44.006
Do you even know anymore?

45:47.031 --> 45:50.198
The truth is I have no choice, Niko.

45:51.148 --> 45:55.173
If she wants a life
without me, I'll accept it.

45:55.175 --> 45:58.592
But I would die to see her one more time.

46:02.690 --> 46:05.187
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC)

46:05.189 --> 46:07.689
(ULY PANTING)

46:28.370 --> 46:31.287
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

46:34.547 --> 46:35.714
So what now?

46:39.460 --> 46:40.744
(UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC)

46:40.746 --> 46:41.579
Now?

47:04.413 --> 47:06.413
You know, being a dog.

47:07.563 --> 47:08.896
Loyal, remember?

47:13.730 --> 47:16.147
- Tomorrow.
- Is nearly here.

47:17.829 --> 47:21.412
The anniversary of
Taurus City will happen.

47:22.584 --> 47:25.584
Your father has organized everything

47:26.859 --> 47:29.859
and he really wants you by his side.

47:37.339 --> 47:38.172
What?

47:40.552 --> 47:43.385
If your drug dealer lets you down,

47:44.219 --> 47:47.131
it's about boarded, taxed.

47:47.133 --> 47:48.300
Totally legal.

47:51.530 --> 47:54.447
Doctor gave me them for my anxiety.

47:56.601 --> 48:00.101
Hard to imagine Tony Heald with anxiety.

48:05.124 --> 48:07.124
It's been seven years.

48:15.264 --> 48:18.363
You've never met him, have you?

48:18.365 --> 48:19.365
TONY: No.

48:22.424 --> 48:23.591
He was free.

48:30.183 --> 48:33.516
Holding his hand was like flying a kite.

48:38.676 --> 48:42.259
Only the wind knew
where it would take him.

48:47.172 --> 48:49.672
Love is the strangest thing.

48:51.560 --> 48:54.010
It's a gear, you know.

48:54.012 --> 48:56.660
People can see they love you,

48:56.662 --> 48:59.245
but how do you know it's there?

49:03.391 --> 49:06.308
I don't think I've ever been loved.

49:07.994 --> 49:08.994
But you are.

49:11.850 --> 49:14.167
Until the end, I'll look after you.

49:14.169 --> 49:16.252
Like you were, as always.

49:21.829 --> 49:24.496
He is not gonna be here forever.

49:29.344 --> 49:32.426
All this one day is going to be mine.

49:38.958 --> 49:41.041
I want to look after you.

49:44.717 --> 49:46.800
I wanna take care of you.

49:54.967 --> 49:58.217
You don't have to worry about anything.

50:07.861 --> 50:08.861
Thank you.

50:18.801 --> 50:21.218
(SOFT MUSIC)

50:29.550 --> 50:32.300
(SIRENS WAILING)

50:46.729 --> 50:49.117
Your report says you fired
the round that killed Marino.

50:49.119 --> 50:50.869
It's true, Captain.

50:51.934 --> 50:54.184
I drew on Johnny Ferro and,

50:56.958 --> 50:59.541
I had my gun down for a second.

51:03.140 --> 51:03.971
And then...

51:03.973 --> 51:07.211
This the kind of event that
destroys careers, Detective.

51:07.213 --> 51:11.615
I think you're confused,
concussions do that shit,

51:11.617 --> 51:12.448
they scramble your brain.

51:12.450 --> 51:15.458
I think what really happened
was you lost your gun

51:15.460 --> 51:20.042
in the fight, and Johnny
Ferro killed Detective Marino.

51:21.498 --> 51:24.362
That's not how it went down.

51:24.364 --> 51:28.447
Try a little pragmatism
here, Detective Delfin.

51:29.884 --> 51:34.217
Pragmatism is the one
thing that Marino taught me.

51:38.629 --> 51:41.212
You should have shot the dog.

51:45.682 --> 51:48.265
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

51:52.982 --> 51:54.532
You expected me to walk it back here

51:54.534 --> 51:57.034
after you sent me into a trap?

52:01.905 --> 52:06.405
An address staked out by
two Taurus City detectives.

52:08.945 --> 52:10.944
ULY: So you did know.

52:13.087 --> 52:14.920
I didn't kill any...

52:15.793 --> 52:16.626
Shit.

52:58.834 --> 53:01.036
Put it down!
(GUN FIRES)

53:01.038 --> 53:01.871
Enough!

53:06.055 --> 53:08.338
(GUN FIRES)

53:08.340 --> 53:10.090
That was a warning.

53:11.478 --> 53:12.395
Let him up.

53:18.593 --> 53:19.426
Baby.

53:20.679 --> 53:21.679
It's done.

53:23.649 --> 53:24.732
AEO: Done?

53:25.648 --> 53:26.815
- No baby.
- No?

53:28.608 --> 53:31.025
This, this, this, this, this?

53:36.063 --> 53:36.980
Let him up!

53:40.055 --> 53:43.212
- Give me the gun.
- I said go.

53:43.214 --> 53:46.881
Go!
(UPBEAT DRAMATIC MUSIC)

53:54.115 --> 53:54.948
Uly!

54:06.495 --> 54:11.495
AEO: Fuck you (SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE).

54:12.290 --> 54:15.207
(PUNCHES THUDDING)

54:31.743 --> 54:34.076
(SCREAMING)

54:40.301 --> 54:42.149
ULY: Where's Penelope?

54:42.151 --> 54:44.568
(AEO LAUGHS)

54:55.618 --> 54:56.618
Suck this!

55:09.833 --> 55:11.666
You're already dead.

55:16.477 --> 55:20.431
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

55:20.433 --> 55:23.266
(CROWD CHEERING)

55:26.583 --> 55:27.416
Get in!

55:31.287 --> 55:35.178
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

55:35.180 --> 55:37.597
(SOFT MUSIC)

55:45.979 --> 55:47.960
Why did you help?

55:47.962 --> 55:50.295
You were kind to me, once.

55:52.609 --> 55:55.192
You really, you don't remember?

56:00.013 --> 56:00.846
Pieces.

56:01.987 --> 56:03.570
Nothing's in order.

56:05.955 --> 56:07.873
Where you taking us?

56:07.875 --> 56:08.965
Yeah, where are we going?

56:08.967 --> 56:09.884
A friend.

56:11.265 --> 56:13.098
- Yours or mine?
- No,

56:17.532 --> 56:19.782
she's not a friend of mine.

56:23.789 --> 56:25.550
But it could be one of the
only places in the city

56:25.552 --> 56:26.802
you'll be safe.

56:37.305 --> 56:39.222
I won't be coming back.

56:40.864 --> 56:42.614
You know why, Johnny?

56:44.882 --> 56:47.965
Change is everything I've ever known.

56:54.398 --> 56:58.148
It's my adaptation, it's
what I do to survive

57:02.431 --> 57:05.348
in a world that I wasn't built for.

57:13.619 --> 57:17.060
Whatever kindness I showed you,

57:17.062 --> 57:18.812
you more than repaid.

57:23.683 --> 57:24.516
Thank you.

57:30.288 --> 57:32.705
HERMES: Good luck, Johnny.

58:27.527 --> 58:30.694
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

58:36.547 --> 58:38.214
I know this place.

58:40.441 --> 58:42.024
Of course you do.

58:54.873 --> 58:57.706
(BANGING ON DOOR)

58:58.966 --> 59:00.575
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

59:00.577 --> 59:03.077
(LIGHT MUSIC)

59:11.612 --> 59:12.695
ULY: Niko?

59:54.323 --> 59:55.573
Johnny Ferro.

59:58.952 --> 59:59.785
Cici.

01:00:17.711 --> 01:00:19.544
Where have you been?

01:00:24.425 --> 01:00:26.925
In my head, nothing's right.

01:00:32.583 --> 01:00:36.148
I don't remember things I should,

01:00:36.150 --> 01:00:39.045
and the things I do remember,

01:00:39.047 --> 01:00:41.380
they're broken up, confused.

01:00:47.182 --> 01:00:49.099
CICI: You need rest.

01:00:57.688 --> 01:00:59.741
Were we lovers?

01:00:59.743 --> 01:01:01.910
One of us loved, anyway.

01:01:07.136 --> 01:01:08.053
Penelope?

01:01:09.745 --> 01:01:11.336
Yes.

01:01:11.338 --> 01:01:15.838
Every time you came back
from the war, you were worse.

01:01:19.550 --> 01:01:22.217
You changed and she was unhappy.

01:01:24.166 --> 01:01:25.833
- I changed?
- Drugs.

01:01:30.436 --> 01:01:32.516
I was a drug dealer.

01:01:32.518 --> 01:01:34.518
You were the best one.

01:01:35.684 --> 01:01:38.528
Michael Ocean's golden boy.

01:01:38.530 --> 01:01:40.835
You used to watch product
move around the Middle East

01:01:40.837 --> 01:01:43.254
during his military missions.

01:01:46.484 --> 01:01:49.025
But one day something happened.

01:01:49.027 --> 01:01:52.526
Your love for her, your rebellious spirit.

01:01:54.688 --> 01:01:57.914
You saw something that changed your life,

01:01:57.916 --> 01:02:00.861
and you became the Prince of the City.

01:02:00.863 --> 01:02:03.077
Prince of the city.

01:02:03.079 --> 01:02:05.662
And Mr. Ocean didn't like it.

01:02:08.611 --> 01:02:11.611
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:02:19.373 --> 01:02:20.206
Johnny.

01:02:24.039 --> 01:02:24.872
Kiss me.

01:02:34.790 --> 01:02:36.373
ULY: Time to go.

01:02:38.090 --> 01:02:40.507
You can stay here, with me.

01:02:43.911 --> 01:02:45.160
You'll be safe.

01:02:46.937 --> 01:02:50.270
I'll take care of you, I'll protect you.

01:02:54.059 --> 01:02:54.892
Stay here.

01:02:56.599 --> 01:02:58.728
What kind of a man would I be then?

01:02:58.730 --> 01:03:01.313
CICI: Any kind you wanna be.

01:03:13.504 --> 01:03:14.337
I can't.

01:03:17.430 --> 01:03:18.263
Why?

01:03:20.612 --> 01:03:21.445
Penelope?

01:03:23.645 --> 01:03:27.312
- I have to find her.
